headline: Broadcom earnings, Fed, Nintendo Switch 2: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime hosts Julie Hyman and Josh Lipton preview the top market stories and headlines Wall Street will be paying attention to tomorrow, Thursday, June 5, including earnings from Broadcom (AVGO), Lululemon Athletica (LULU), and Victoria's Secret (VSCO), commentary from Federal Reserve officials, and the release of Nintendo's (NTDOY, 7974.T) widely anticipated Switch 2 game console at midnight. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here.
